context: <a0_0><b6_0>The number of entrants has increased <b5_0>greatly<b5_0/> in recent years<b6_0/><a0_0/>. In the <b8_0>2004–05<b8_0/> season, <a1_0>660 clubs entered the competition<a1_0/>, beating the long-standing record of 656 from the 1921–22 season. In 2005–06 this increased to <a2_0>674<a2_0/> entrants, in 2006–07 to <a3_0>687<a3_0/>, in 2007–08 to <a4_0>731<a4_0/> clubs, and for the 2008–09 and 2009–10 competitions it reached 762. <b7_0>The number has varied slightly but remained roughly stable since<b7_0/> then, with 759 clubs participating in 2010–11, a record 763 in 2011–12, 758 for 2012–13, 737 for 2013–14 and 736 for 2014–15.
